Plotting (Line graph) with Exponential (x^2) graph¶

In [89]:
x=[0,1,2,3,4,5]        # giving range for x-axis (Line graph) 
y=[0,2,4,6,8,10]       # giving range for y-axis (Line graph)

# Plotting x^2 graph
x2=np.arange(0,4.5,0.5)                       # x-axis range for (x^2) graph
plt.plot(x2[:6],x2[:6]**2,'b',label='X^2')    # plot first part of (x^2) as normal line with blue colour
plt.plot(x2[5:],x2[5:]**2,'b--')              # plot second part of (x^2) as dashed line with blue colour

# Labelling Y-axis, X-axis, and Title
plt.title('Line Graph vs Exp. Graph',fontdict={ 'fontname':'Comic Sans MS','fontsize':18})
plt.xlabel('X Axis')
plt.ylabel('Y Axis')

# scale mark of graph
plt.xticks([0,1,2,3,4,5])
plt.yticks([0,2,4,6,8,10,12,14])

# Plotting Line Graph
plt.plot(x,y,'rD--',label='2x')          # 'r.--'  Color, Marker, Line
plt.legend()
plt.show()
plt.savefig('Line Graph_1.png',dpi=300)   # dpi =300 good when saving when graph has high resolution

<Figure size 640x480 with 0 Axes>

plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))     # dimensions of the figure
plt.title('Gas Prices over Time (in USD)',fontdict={'fontweight':'bold','fontsize':16})  # title name with bold-text and fontsize 16

# Plotting 'USA', 'Canada', 'South Korea' Columns with 'Year' Column
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas.USA,'b.-',label='USA')       # 'b.-' --> Color Marker Line    
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas.Canada,'r*--',label='Canada')     # 'r*--' --> Color Marker Line
plt.plot(gas.Year,gas['South Korea'],color='green',label='South Korea')

# Another way to plot many values using FOR Loop
# countries_to_look_at=['Australia','USA','Canada','South Korea']
# for country in countries_to_look_at:
#     plt.plot(gas.Year,gas[country],marker='.')

plt.xticks(gas.Year[::3],)    # skip in X-axis EVERY 3 Years
plt.legend()
plt.xlabel('Year',fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Prices in $',fontsize=14)
plt.savefig('Gas Price Figure.png',dpi=300)
plt.show()

Plotting Pie Chart_2¶

In [27]:
# to remove/separate 'lbs' from 'Weight Column'  and check if there is no string, just leave it as it is
fifa.Weight= [int(x.strip('lbs')) if type(x)==str else x for x in fifa.Weight]

plt.style.use('ggplot')    # coloring styling for Pie Chart

# specifing weights into categories
light=fifa.loc[fifa.Weight<125].count()[0]                                     # heavy_weight = weight < 125lbs
light_medium=fifa.loc[(fifa.Weight>=125) & (fifa.Weight<150)].count()[0]       # heavy_weight = weight >= 125lbs & < 150lbs
medium=fifa.loc[(fifa.Weight>=150) & (fifa.Weight<175)].count()[0]             # heavy_weight = weight >= 150lbs & < 175lbs
medium_heavy=fifa.loc[(fifa.Weight>=175) & (fifa.Weight<200)].count()[0]       # heavy_weight = weight >= 175lbs & < 200lbs
heavy=fifa.loc[fifa.Weight>=200].count()[0]                                    # heavy_weight = weight >= 200lbs

weights=[light, light_medium, medium, medium_heavy, heavy]          # making an array of specified weights for easy plotting
labels=['Under 125','125-150','150-175','175-200','Over 200']       # labels of weights to appear on on pie chart
explode=(.4, .2, 0, 0, .4)                                          # separating slices in pie chart for clear readings

plt.title('Weight Distribution of FIFA Players (in lbs)')
plt.pie(weights,labels=labels,autopct='%.2f %%',explode=explode)       # plotting percentages of different weight categories
plt.show()
plt.savefig('Pie Chart_2.png',dpi=300)

PLotting BoxPlot¶

Box Plot with (FCB & Real Madrid) Clubs with their Player's Overall Performance¶

In [36]:
plt.style.use('default')
plt.figure(figsize=(5,8))

barcelona=fifa.loc[fifa.Club=='FC Barcelona']['Overall']
madrid=fifa.loc[fifa.Club=='Real Madrid'] ['Overall']
revs= fifa.loc[fifa.Club=='New England Revolution']['Overall']

labels=['FC Barcelona ','Real Madrid','NE Revolution']

boxes= plt.boxplot([barcelona,madrid,revs],labels=labels,patch_artist=True,medianprops={'linewidth':4})    # to style each individual box
for box in boxes['boxes']:
    box.set(color='#4286f4')         # to set edge colour
    box.set(facecolor='#e0e0e0')     # to change fill colour 

plt.title('Professional Soccer Team Comparison')
plt.ylabel('FIFA Overall Rating')
plt.show()
plt.savefig('Box Plot.png',dpi=300)
